#!/usr/bin/env testml


*jsc.validate(*json) == *valid


=== Test 1 - pattern validation - a matching pattern is valid
--- valid: true
--- jsc
{"pattern": "^a*$"}
--- json
"aaa"


=== Test 2 - pattern validation - a non-matching pattern is invalid
--- valid: false
--- ^jsc
--- json
"abc"


=== Test 3 - pattern validation - ignores non-strings
--- valid: true
--- ^jsc
--- json
true


=== Test 4 - pattern is not anchored - matches a substring
--- valid: true
--- jsc
{"pattern": "a+"}
--- json
"xxaayy"


# vim: ft=testml sw=2:
